Class PayrollProcessing

  • java.lang.Object
    • PayrollProcessing

  • public class PayrollProcessing
extends java.lang.Object
    User facing class that allows for the operation of the program. Performs all functions associated with creating a payroll, including the addition and removal of parttime/fulltime/management employees, as well as specific operations to each type of employee. This class also allows the user to print employee information based on date hired, department, or array order.
    Author:
    Craig Li, Prerak Patel

    • Method Detail

      • run

        public void run()
        Interface that reads from user input, and performs actions based on commands given. Actions allowed are addition/removal of parttime/fulltime/management employees, setting hours of parttime employees, calculating payments, and printing based on different sorting methods.

      • isDeptValid

        private boolean isDeptValid(java.lang.String dept)
        Checks if provided department is valid based on the three given in the assignment. The only valid departments are CS, ECE, and IT.

        Returns:
